dismissalText.commentary: David Hussey run out (Dilshan) 29 (41b 5x4 0x6 76m) SR: 70.73

dismissalComment.html: run-out, turns it into the leg side just a little square of midwicket, Dilshan is the man there, he moved to his right, slid, collected it and threw down the stumps at the non-striker's end, Mendis thought of collecting the throw initially but decided to let it be in the end as it was on its way to the stumps, Hussey is gone, this is a huge blow for Australia, Hussey called for a single, there was some hesitation and he was caught short in the end

Well taken at midwicket by Thirimanne, short and it was nicely picked by Bailey, seized the length early and pulled it well but found Thirimanne, who leapt, timed his jump right, intercepted it and took a sharp one. The umpire was checking for a no-ball and replays show Malinga had a tiny part of his foot behind the line at the time of landing, so all good there, Australia have lost ther third

headshotImage.caption: Ben Cutting player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Cutting player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: gone! Malinga strikes, Perera takes his third catch, pitched up outside off and Cutting tries to drive it through cover, gets a thick edge and Perera dives to his right to snap that one

headshotImage.caption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kane Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Oh dear, a first baller on debut, a deceptive slower one from Malinga, Richardson didn't spot it, it died low on the batsman and Richardson missed it to be struck low on the pad, perhaps just in line with leg stump, he's got to go

dismissalText.commentary: Phillip Hughes lbw b Kulasekara 3 (14b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 21.42

dismissalComment.html: appeal for lbw and he's given, Hughes has called for a review, he showed his bat immediately after it struck him on the pads, seemed like it landed on leg and Hughes tried to work it square, missed, no impact with the bat at all, Hot Spot doesn't capture anything, and it would have gone on to hit middle and off, that's plumb, Erasmus has made the right call

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

commentTextItems.html: Reaches his century and scores the inning runs as well, short and he makes room to cut that past point to complete the formalities, it's his first List A century, he's relieved, takes off his helmet, acknowledges the applause and then shakes hands with the hosts, the series is level 1-1

commentPostTextItems.html: A comfortable win for Sri Lanka, each team dominating a game this series. The bowlers first did the job, and Dilshan and Thirimanne ensured there were no major hiccups in the chase of 171. Daniel Brettig's report should be ready soon. We don't have any coverage of the presentation. Thanks for tuning in and sending us your feedback, and we'll be back with you for the third ODI on January 18 which will be played in Brisbane. See you then.

commentTextItems.html: slightly short, turns in, he calmly defends it towards silly point

headshotImage.caption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021

commentTextItems.html: shortish on middle and it's played towards midwicket
quicker through the air, on the off stump and he defends it on the pitch
gets forward and outside the line and he defends
takes a single, drives it wide of midwicket, a fumble and they have to take a single
Thirimanne takes a chance and gets a boundary, that was tossed up and he came down, got to the pitch and swung it into that gap between long-on and deep midwicket
drives that one straight back to the bowler, Thirimanne still stands a chance

headshotImage.caption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021

commentTextItems.html: an inside edge on the pads for Perera, rolls down towards short fine
comes down the pitch and takes a single by pushing that towards cover
fires that one down the leg side and it's a wide
turns it towards short fine leg for a single
flighted on middle and it's pushed straight to mid-on
tossed up on the off, drives it down the ground to long-off and he takes single
slightly short on the off, turns it behind square for a single to keep strike

commentPostTextItems.html: Nine more to go for a century, 12 to wiin

headshotImage.caption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021

commentTextItems.html: slightly short on middle, turns it into the leg side for a single
pitched up outside off, plenty of width and Perera crashes that through extra cover for four more
hard and flat, that's a six, on a length and he swings it hard over the deep square leg boundary, Kane Richardson is a tall man but he couldn't reach it
on a length, reaches forward and defends that into the off side

commentPreTextItems.html: Doherty to bowl now, has a slip

commentTextItems.html: round the wicket, short outside off, crunched past point for a single

dismissalText.commentary: Phillip Hughes lbw b Kulasekara 3 (14b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 21.42

dismissalComment.html: appeal for lbw and he's given, Hughes has called for a review, he showed his bat immediately after it struck him on the pads, seemed like it landed on leg and Hughes tried to work it square, missed, no impact with the bat at all, Hot Spot doesn't capture anything, and it would have gone on to hit middle and off, that's plumb, Erasmus has made the right call

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey c Thirimanne b Malinga 26 (46b 2x4 1x6 56m) SR: 56.52

dismissalComment.html: Well taken at midwicket by Thirimanne, short and it was nicely picked by Bailey, seized the length early and pulled it well but found Thirimanne, who leapt, timed his jump right, intercepted it and took a sharp one. The umpire was checking for a no-ball and replays show Malinga had a tiny part of his foot behind the line at the time of landing, so all good there, Australia have lost ther third

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith c MDKJ Perera b NLTC Perera 8 (11b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 72.72

dismissalComment.html: Smith goes! A thin inside edge as he goes for the drive, pitched on a length outside off and Smith tried to go hard at that through extra cover, it came back in just a hint, and Smith got a thin inside edge through to the keeper

dismissalText.commentary: David Hussey run out (Dilshan) 29 (41b 5x4 0x6 76m) SR: 70.73

dismissalComment.html: run-out, turns it into the leg side just a little square of midwicket, Dilshan is the man there, he moved to his right, slid, collected it and threw down the stumps at the non-striker's end, Mendis thought of collecting the throw initially but decided to let it be in the end as it was on its way to the stumps, Hussey is gone, this is a huge blow for Australia, Hussey called for a single, there was some hesitation and he was caught short in the end

dismissalComment.html: Six down! Mathews strikes, lovely delivery, just outside off stump, drew the batsman forward with a good length and got it to nip away just a touch, Maxwell was committed to the drive as he walked forward, got a thin edge and Perera made no mistake behind the stumps

dismissalComment.html: Oh dear, a first baller on debut, a deceptive slower one from Malinga, Richardson didn't spot it, it died low on the batsman and Richardson missed it to be struck low on the pad, perhaps just in line with leg stump, he's got to go

dismissalText.commentary: Clint McKay c MDKJ Perera b NLTC Perera 4 (11b 0x4 0x6 15m) SR: 36.36

dismissalComment.html: appeal for a catch, short of a good length outside off, tries to open the face there to play it past point, it's given not out but the Sri Lankans have reviewed it, Hot Spot shows no heat signature, the umpire is taking his time to decide this, no real sound in live motion, the appeal was spontaneous but no strong technical evidence there of a deflection. Would you believe it, that's been given out. Surprise all around, McKay is surprised, the decision has been overturned.
